name: House Sparrow
description: House Sparrows are ubiquitous birds, you will probably find them wherever you find people. Endlessly calling, I hear them more than I see them. This particular sparrow is part of a family living under the roof tiles of the house opposite, and now that I think about it, it’s likely there’s a family under our own roof as well. | 2592x3888px | f/8, 1/500s, 300mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 26th May 2021 just outside my house in Brighton, England
